notesStmt.note: Title from title page (f. 1r) and spine.

msContents.summary: Extensive work on chemistry in 137 chapters, preceded by tables of chemical symbols (f. 2r-6v) that are used in the text throughout the manuscript.

supportDesc.extent: 324 leaves : 257 x 205 (225 x 155) mm. bound to 257 x 205 mm

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 26-35 long lines; some verticals marked by folding; no inner margins.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a German cursive (Fraktur) script, by Anton Ruprecht.

origin.p: Written in Chemnitz in eastern Germany (the attribution on the title page places it in Hungary), in 1784 (f. 1r).

history.provenance: Formerly in the library of the Franklin Institute, Philadelphia, acc. no. 6748 (bookplate inside upper cover; accession number in ink, f. 2r).
Sold by F. Thomas Heller, Inc. (Swarthmore, Pa.), 1995.
Formerly owned by John D. Stanitz (Cleveland, Ohio), Ms. 45.
Acquired by Lawrence J. Schoenberg with other Stanitz manuscripts, Sept. 1997.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2011.
